      <text>10.1.4 (Finding derivatives from first principals)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the derivative of the function \(f(x)= x^3\) from first principals.</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We use the definition of the derivative as follows:
\[
\begin{align*}
\mbox{gradient } &= \lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{f({@xh@}) -f(x)}{h}
\\
&= \lim\limits_{h \to 0} \frac{{@f1@} - {@func@}}{h}
\\
&= \lim\limits_{h \to 0} {@lim1@}
\\
&=\lim\limits_{h \to 0} ({@lim2@})
\\
&= {@ta1@}
\end{align*}
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
